snippet.title: Investigating Surface Area of a Cone | Area of a Circle Plus Area of a Circle (Kinda)
snippet.description:
http://tapintoteenminds.com Investigating the Surface Area of a Cone.  In this video, we explore where the surface area of a cone formula comes from.  While it is not an algebraic proof, this video intends to bring some context as to why the formula is (Pi)(r^2) + Pi(r)(s) using an example where the height of the cone is 0.

Have another interesting way to add some context to this formula?  Please let everyone know in the comments!
